      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Interest on student loans is generally calculated on the remaining principal balance each month. When you make a payment, it first covers the accrued interest, and the rest goes towards reducing the principal. If interest is high relative to your payment, a larger portion of your monthly payment goes to interest rather than lowering the balance quickly. This explains why your principal balance might not be decreasing as fast as you expected.",
